Sibusiso Tede (20) is a happy young man after receiving his ID on Tuesday. The People’s Paper published Sibusiso’s story on 8 February headlined: “Sibusiso is sent from pillar to post.” The young man from Emalahleni, Mpumalanaga, has been battling to get his ID since he applied for one in 2017. Sibusiso told Daily Sun that he now feels like a complete citizen. He said when he received an SMS from Home Affairs about his ID, it felt great. “I’d like to thank Daily Sun for publishing my story. I’m so grateful. “The paper has found a way to give my life meaning.” He said his dream is to study actuarial science next year. “I’ll apply for bursaries but in the meantime I’m looking for a job.”